      "writtenOn": "2020-11-10T16:57:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "PictureImage is not free to draw, as we will *always* first apply-the-picture to another buffer, so that we have resolved pixels (and then try to cache that). Seems like just \"fixing\" the pixels at decode time is just as cheap or cheaper. Was there another consideration for taking this deferred/picture approach?",
      "revId": "f369f74111f0522df8f06d4b1d86b87f5dfc1167",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5acbeffa_66d9321e",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-10T17:16:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. Let\u0027s say we have an image with a non-default orientation, we want to decode frame B, and B depends on A. If A is already stored, and we\u0027ve fixed its pixels, we need to unfix them in order to apply the update from B, then re-fix the final output.\n\nI was thinking the PictureImage would be a simpler fix for what is likely an uncommon case, but perhaps doing the unfix is not so bad?",
      "parentUuid": "938c3149_bba7e290",
      "revId": "f369f74111f0522df8f06d4b1d86b87f5dfc1167",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b72ca48a_9b49d1f3",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5649
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-10T17:24:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah. \"apply the update\" -- I guess B is some delta applied to A? Can the delta be rotated? (I hadn\u0027t thought about this aspect).",
      "parentUuid": "5acbeffa_66d9321e",
      "revId": "f369f74111f0522df8f06d4b1d86b87f5dfc1167",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7f9b8517_843bf0c3",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-10T19:06:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Ah. \"apply the update\" -- I guess B is some delta applied to A?\n\nYes. Typically B will be a rectangle that blends with A (although APNG, which we don\u0027t currently support, and WebP have an option that essentially says to use SkBlendMode::kSrc). It\u0027s also possible that A is a subset delta that depends on another frame, and if it\u0027s marked kRestoreBGColor, we need to erase its delta to transparent black before we blend B.\n\nThinking on this some more, instead of \"unfixing\" A, we could just decode the rectangle for B into zeroed memory and draw it through the matrix into the already-fixed A. (For the kRestoreBGColor case, we would need to run A\u0027s rectangle through the matrix before erase, too.)\n\n\u003e Can the delta be rotated? (I hadn\u0027t thought about this aspect).\n\nI\u0027m not aware of a case where the delta would be rotated relative to other frames.",
      "parentUuid": "b72ca48a_9b49d1f3",
      "revId": "f369f74111f0522df8f06d4b1d86b87f5dfc1167",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "462bc221_fbb09d92",
        "filename": "src/utils/SkAnimCodecPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 100,
